The paper discusses a new consensus protocol for blockchain, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The paper focuses on security, scalability, and decentralization, which are important issues in cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed protocol involves the use of microblocks and macroblocks, which are related to network protocols (cs.NI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses mechanisms for reducing transaction overlapping and limiting a leader's power, which are topics in control systems (cs.SY).
